sa_col <- c(2,11,15,22,26:29,59:60,77,94:95,115:116) #identify columns containing short answer responses
dem_col <- c(96:111) #identify columns containing demographic information

#isolate only multiple choice responses and rename column names
mc <- raw %>%
  select(c(-sa_col, -dem_col)) %>% #remove short answer responses and demographic information
  rename_all(~str_replace(.,"there_are_many_factors_that_can_have_an_effect_on_someones_well_being_please_identify_how_important_the_following_items_are_to_your_personal_well_being", "factors")) %>%
  rename_all(~str_replace(.,"we_would_like_to_identify_eem_bs_strengths_and_weaknesses_in_supporting_graduate_student_wellness_please_identify_how_available_each_item_is_based_on_your_experience_as_a_graduate_student_in_eemb", "eemb_strengths_weaknesses")) %>%
  rename_all(~str_replace(.,"many_things_can_affect_our_progress_and_well_being_during_graduate_school_please_identify_the_extent_to_which_you_feel_comfortable_discussing_the_following_issues_with_your_advisor_s", "advisor_comfort")) %>%
  rename_all(~str_replace(.,"do_you_think_any_of_the_following_are_issues_in_the_eemb_department", "eemb_issues")) %>%
  rename_all(~str_replace(.,"how_comfortable_do_you_feel_talking_openly_about_dei_issues_with", "dei_conversations")) %>%
  rename_all(~str_replace(.,"do_you_feel_well_supported", "support")) %>%
  rename("respondent_id"=1, #rename individual columns too long but without repetitive strings
         "discrimination_resources_yn"=19,
         "eemb_dei_meeting_frequency"=22,

# Unique questions
unique_Qs <- unique(headings[multi_solo=='multi',(question)]) # List to store graphs
graphs_multi_race <- list()

# Loop by question (in a slightly weird way so that we can store all graphs in lists)
for(i in 1:length(unique_Qs)){
# For some questions, respondents did not collectively select all the possible options,
# so we will set up each variable as a factor with the same levels.
# That way, each plot for a given question will have the same answers in the same order
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "How comfortable do you feel talking openly about DEI issues with:"){
    levels <- c("Uncomfortable", "Neutral", 
                "Comfortable","Unsure")}
  
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "Do you feel well supported:"){
    levels <- c("No","Somewhat","Yes","Unsure")}
  
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "Do you think any of the following are issues in the EEMB department?"){
    levels <- c("No","Somewhat","Yes","Unsure")}
  
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "I know what resources are available to me if I am discriminated 
     against or witness discrimination against someone else"){
    levels <- c("No","Somewhat","Yes","Unsure")}
  
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "I would feel comfortable using these resources"){
    levels <- c("No","Somewhat","Yes","Unsure")}
  
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "Did you sign the petition?"){
    levels <- c("No","Yes")}  
  
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "How often do you think the department should hold department-wide meetings on DEI?"){
    levels <- c("Never", "Once a year","Twice a year","Once a quarter","Multiple times per quarter")}

  if(unique_Qs[i] == "Are you co-advised?"){
    levels <- c("No","Yes")}  

  if(unique_Qs[i] == "How is your relationship(s) with your advisor(s)?"){
    levels <- c("Poor","Fair","Good")}
  
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "Please identify the extent to which you feel comfortable discussing the following issues with your advisor(s):"){
    levels <- c("Uncomfortable", "Neutral", 
                "Comfortable","Unsure")}
    
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "My advisor:"){
    levels <- c("Disagree", "Neutral", 
                "Agree","Unsure")}

  if(unique_Qs[i] == "Please identify how important the following items are to your personal well-being:"){
    levels <- c("Not important", "Neutral", 
                "Important","Unsure")}

  if(unique_Qs[i] == "Please identify how available each item is based on your experience as a graduate student in EEMB:"){
    levels <- c("Lacking", "Room for Improvement", "Available", "Unsure")}
  
  if(unique_Qs[i] == "First Priority"){
    levels <- c("Financial support", "Mental health support", "Departmental climate", 
                "Departmental transparency", "Faculty advising/mentorship",
                "Peer mentorship","Professional/skills development",
                "Program requirements/structure")}
  
    if(unique_Qs[i] == "Second Priority"){
    levels <- c("Financial support", "Mental health support", "Departmental climate", 
                "Departmental transparency", "Faculty advising/mentorship",
                "Peer mentorship","Professional/skills development",
                "Program requirements/structure")}

    if(unique_Qs[i] == "Third Priority"){
    levels <- c("Financial support", "Mental health support", "Departmental climate", 
                "Departmental transparency", "Faculty advising/mentorship",
                "Peer mentorship","Professional/skills development",
                "Program requirements/structure")}
  
  
# Get index of columns  associated to a main question
sub_cols <- unlist(headings[which(headings$question==unique_Qs[i]), "col_index"])

# Manual reshape of data from wide to long (WHITE RESPONDENTS)
d_i <- data.table(y= factor(as.vector(as.matrix(mc[,c(sub_cols)])), levels=levels),
                  x= rep(headings$sub_category[sub_cols-1], each=nrow(mc)),
                  race = rep(mc$ethnicity_white_vs_mixed_race_vs_people_of_color,
                             length(headings$sub_category[sub_cols-1])))

d_i <- d_i[is.na(d_i$race)==F]

# Format dataset
d_i$x <- str_wrap(d_i$x, width=40)
d_i <- d_i[,.N, by=c("y","x","race")]
setorderv(d_i, c("x","N"))
d_i$x <- factor(d_i$x, levels = rev(unique(d_i$x)))
d_i$race <- factor(d_i$race, levels = )

p_i <-
  ggplot(data = d_i,
       aes(x=N,y=x,fill=y))+ theme_bw()+
    geom_bar(stat='identity', position ='fill')+
    facet_wrap(.~race)+
    labs(title=str_wrap(unique_Qs[i], width=50))+
    theme(axis.title.y = element_blank(),
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        legend.title = element_blank(),
        title = element_text(size=10, face = 'bold', hjust=-1),
        panel.spacing.x = unit(1, 'lines'))

ggsave(p_i,  filename = here::here("2021", "demographic_responses_graphs", "POC", paste(unique_Qs[i], "png", sep = "."))) # This line saves each plot that the for loop generates

graphs_multi_race[[i]] <- p_i

}

graphs_multi_race
